# JavaScript Rules

## Namespace Pattern
Each tool page has its own namespace exposed on `window`:
```javascript
var CalcTools = window.CalcTools = window.CalcTools || {};
CalcTools.calculate = function () { /* ... */ };
```
| Page | Namespace |
|------|-----------|
| tools.html | `SnakeTools` |
| units.html | `SnakeUnits` |
| calc.html | `CalcTools` |
| dev.html | `DevTools` |
| color.html | `ColorTools` |

## Function Rules
- Validate inputs first — if invalid, write an error string to the result container, return early.
- Never `alert()`, `confirm()`, or `prompt()`.
- Result always written to the DOM — never `return` raw values from onclick handlers.
- Use `document.getElementById('...')` — no jQuery.

## Adding a New Tool Function
```javascript
/* ── Tool Name ── */
Namespace.toolName = function () {
  var val = document.getElementById('inputId').value.trim();
  var out = document.getElementById('outputId');
  if (!val) { out.textContent = 'Please enter a value.'; return; }
  out.textContent = /* computation */;
};
```

## i18n in JS
```javascript
// Get translated string
var label = window.PdfMasterI18n.t('key.name');
// Get current language
var lang = window.PdfMasterI18n.getLang(); // 'en' | 'tr'
```

## Snake API (do not modify snake-mascot.js for integrations)
```javascript
window.snakeMascot.onFileSelect();       // wiggle on input
window.snakeMascot.processStart(fn);     // eat → process → spit
window.snakeMascot.snackFile();          // eat one file (adds bump)
```
